19:24.990 --> 19:26.423
with the after-care teacher.
They're fine.

19:26.460 --> 19:28.792
Kent, Jamal needed
an ice pack for his lip.

19:28.830 --> 19:30.388
So this boy puts his hands
on my son?

19:30.430 --> 19:31.624
Jamal was the _one
d0ing the teasmg.

19:31.670 --> 19:33.194
He pushed Blue.

19:33.240 --> 19:34.798
And that's reason for him
to hit my son in the face?

19:34.840 --> 19:36.535
We all need to calm down.

19:36.570 --> 19:37.764
Isn't Blue the boy
that plays with
the Barbie doll?

19:37.810 --> 19:39.266
It ain't a Barbie doll.

19:39.310 --> 19:40.504
Maybe if you bought your son
the appropriate toys,

19:40.540 --> 19:42.269
he'd fit in better
with the other boys--

19:42.310 --> 19:43.709
Ain't none of your business
what toys my son plays with.

19:43.750 --> 19:44.944
Now I see why he hit Jamal.

19:44.980 --> 19:47.414
I told Blue to defend
himself against bullies.

19:47.450 --> 19:49.418
Maybe if you taught
your son some manners,

19:49.450 --> 19:51.213
our son wouldn't have had
to hit yours.

19:51.250 --> 19:53.218
Everyone, please.

19:53.260 --> 19:54.887
Now, we have
a zero tolerance policy

19:54.920 --> 19:56.558
for bullying and violence.

19:56.590 --> 19:59.457
Now, this is a session
for conflict resolution.

20:00.730 --> 20:02.698
Now what?

20:02.730 --> 20:04.425
Talk to your sons.

20:04.470 --> 20:05.960
Encourage them
to talk to a teacher

20:06.000 --> 20:08.560
the next time that a problem
comes up in the future.

20:08.600 --> 20:11.569
And know that if a problem
does come up in the future

20:11.610 --> 20:13.430
from either
of these students,

20:13.480 --> 20:14.879
whether it's bullying
or violence

20:14.910 --> 20:16.468
we're going to be
dealing with suspension.

20:16.510 --> 20:19.377
This is a warning
for all of us.

20:20.980 --> 20:22.470
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

20:27.660 --> 20:29.252
( scoffs )

20:31.560 --> 20:33.721
I'm very sorry
I didn't catch this sooner.

20:33.760 --> 20:34.897
You're dealing with
a lot of kids.

20:34.930 --> 20:36.022
That's fine.

20:36.060 --> 20:37.664
Thank you for calling me.

20:40.300 --> 20:41.528
Ralph:
Come on.

20:43.910 --> 20:45.798
( door opens )

21:01.020 --> 21:02.612
Didn't hear you
come back.

21:09.530 --> 21:12.419
Thought about what I'd do
ifI had to go back to jail.

21:14.040 --> 21:15.735
I can't do it.

21:18.970 --> 21:21.370
I won't do it.

21:21.410 --> 21:23.799
You're not going to go back
to jail, Too Sweet.

21:23.850 --> 21:25.442
Don't I have
to go to trial?

21:25.480 --> 21:27.414
I don't think they're going
to let this go to trial.

21:27.450 --> 21:29.008
They don't have
any evidence.

21:29.050 --> 21:30.642
All they had
was trumped-up charges.

21:30.690 --> 21:32.646
I've met people that have been
in and out of jail

21:32.690 --> 21:34.658
- their whole lives.
- That ain't going to be you.

21:34.690 --> 21:36.487
We going to get you
back in school.

21:36.520 --> 21:39.557
- They don't want me back.
- Then another school.

21:39.590 --> 21:42.058
But we're going
to get you a degree.

21:42.100 --> 21:44.398
Maybe it'll be a GED,

21:44.430 --> 21:46.921
but you're going
to finish high school,

21:46.970 --> 21:49.336
and then we'll look
for a college.

21:49.370 --> 21:52.339
Or whatever
you want to do.

21:53.110 --> 21:55.977
See the world.
Learn new things.

21:56.010 --> 22:00.049
There's a-- There's a whole
world out there.

22:00.080 --> 22:02.719
And a whole world in here.

22:02.750 --> 22:04.615
And a whole world here.

22:07.050 --> 22:11.350
It's yours and only yours.

22:11.390 --> 22:14.689
No matter what they say,
or what they think,

22:14.730 --> 22:16.698
or where you are.

22:19.100 --> 22:20.636
( sniffles )

22:35.050 --> 22:35.914
( phone beeps )

22:35.950 --> 22:37.212
Remy over phone:
Hey, Charley.

22:37.250 --> 22:40.117
I feel really bad about
what happened with Micah.

22:40.150 --> 22:42.857
But I'd be lying
if I said

22:42.890 --> 22:46.053
I didn't want_
to see you again.

22:46.090 --> 22:50.595
I'd like to talk
about this, okay?

22:50.630 --> 22:51.927
Call me.

22:51.970 --> 22:53.460
( phone beeps )

22:53.500 --> 22:55.934
( footsteps approach )

22:55.970 --> 22:58.006
Wow!

22:58.040 --> 22:59.769
( laughs )

22:59.810 --> 23:02.677
Ooh, you look amazing.

23:02.710 --> 23:06.874
Ooh, champagne brunch
with the dean.

23:06.910 --> 23:10.141
I'm told the guest list
includes the governor's wife,

23:10.180 --> 23:11.738
a congressman.

23:11.790 --> 23:15.180
Owner of the New Orleans
Stingers? What's his name?

23:15.220 --> 23:16.983
Frank Rovnerman?

23:17.020 --> 23:18.681
Fancy, fancy.

23:18.730 --> 23:20.755
I just got to lock up
Micah's admission.

23:20.800 --> 23:23.724
And I need to stop by
the farm first.

23:23.770 --> 23:26.819
Me and Ralph Angel are meeting
with the bank loan rep.

23:28.840 --> 23:31.764
Feels like the minute
I get one thing done,

23:31.810 --> 23:33.630
10 more tasks show up.

23:33.680 --> 23:35.705
Baby, that's life.

23:35.740 --> 23:38.641
At least you're thinking
about yourself

23:38.680 --> 23:40.978
and that fresh start.

23:41.020 --> 23:43.841
Ralph Angel told me
that you filed for divorce.
That's good.

23:43.890 --> 23:49.681
When they don't realize
what they have in us,

23:49.720 --> 23:52.689
when they violate
the love we give,

23:52.730 --> 23:54.823
we got to learn
to cut them loose.

23:59.700 --> 24:04.160
Took me way too long
to learn that with Jimmy Dale.

24:04.210 --> 24:09.739
So, I'm very happy that you're
not making the same mistake.

24:12.610 --> 24:14.077
Thanks, Aunt Vi.

24:15.250 --> 24:17.684
I really needed
to hear that today.

24:20.990 --> 24:23.686
Is Hollywood
in that category?

24:23.730 --> 24:26.153
With Jimmy Dale
and Davis?

24:28.160 --> 24:29.229
No.

24:32.000 --> 24:32.967
No.

24:33.000 --> 24:35.093
You need to talk to him,
Aunt Vi.

24:36.800 --> 24:42.670
Yeah, well, he still out
on the rig now, so...

24:42.710 --> 24:44.871
Morning, Aunt Vi.

24:44.910 --> 24:47.515
- Morning, baby.
- Hi, honey.

24:47.550 --> 24:50.075
I'm going to the mall
with Keke and some
of her friends,

24:50.120 --> 24:52.645
but I will be back tonight
to help you at the High Yellow.

24:52.690 --> 24:54.681
How are you getting
to the mall?

24:54.720 --> 24:56.119
Micah?

24:56.160 --> 24:57.252
( door opens )

24:57.290 --> 24:58.780
Now, what was that all about?

24:58.830 --> 25:01.025
( door closes )

25:02.860 --> 25:05.192
He's giving me
the silent treatment.

25:05.230 --> 25:07.118
- Oh, really?
- Mm-hmm.

25:07.170 --> 25:09.638
Well, you need to give him
the ass-whupping treatment.

25:09.670 --> 25:10.864
( laughs )

25:10.910 --> 25:13.037
Shoot

25:13.070 --> 25:17.109
Baby, they still have you
listed as Charlotte West.

25:17.140 --> 25:20.917
They dropped the Bordelon.
You need to get that fixed.

25:24.020 --> 25:25.180
Good luck.

25:25.220 --> 25:26.585
You, too.

25:26.620 --> 25:27.780
Okay.

25:27.820 --> 25:30.152
The reopening
is going to be great.

25:31.290 --> 25:33.622
It is.

25:33.660 --> 25:34.922
All right.

26:26.780 --> 26:28.668
Can I crack an egg?

26:28.720 --> 26:29.948
Remember what
I told you?

26:29.980 --> 26:32.881
One crack at the side,
then open it quick.

26:35.390 --> 26:36.812
Just like that.

26:36.860 --> 26:38.828
Good job, buddy.
Good job.

26:38.860 --> 26:40.725
So, after breakfast,
what you want to do?

26:40.760 --> 26:42.694
Is Mom coming over?

26:42.730 --> 26:44.061
I don't think so.

26:44.100 --> 26:46.227
She probably has stuff to do
on a Saturday.

26:46.270 --> 26:48.363
Can you ask?

26:48.400 --> 26:49.628
Blue...

26:51.270 --> 26:53.602
you don't want to hang out
with me no more?

26:54.740 --> 26:56.332
What, I'm not good enough?

26:56.380 --> 26:57.847
You're good, Pop,

26:57.880 --> 26:59.973
but I like it when
it's the three of us.

27:01.720 --> 27:03.017
I think that needs
some vanilla.

27:03.050 --> 27:04.938
- Me, too.
- You're making a mess.

27:04.990 --> 27:06.719
- Go ahead, put it in there.
- ( knock on door)

27:06.750 --> 27:08.183
I'm going to stir it.

27:09.420 --> 27:10.853
- Oh, hey.
- Hi.

27:10.890 --> 27:12.926
- Auntie Charley!
- Hi, honey! Whoa, whoa.

27:12.960 --> 27:14.996
Blue, ease up.

27:15.030 --> 27:16.918
Aunt Charley
got her Prada on.

27:16.960 --> 27:19.190
Come on, go wash up.
She don't want to get dirty.

27:19.230 --> 27:21.039
- Okay.
- Wipe that off your face.

27:21.070 --> 27:23.129
- Blue: Okay.
- Bye, baby.

27:25.870 --> 27:28.998
Charley, you need
to see this.

27:29.040 --> 27:30.678
Are these the loan advisor's
assessments?

27:30.710 --> 27:34.009
Yeah. He came out yesterday,
said our acreage looks good.

27:34.050 --> 27:37.269
Our soil composition is deep,
well drained,

27:37.320 --> 27:39.049
no infestation, all that.

27:39.090 --> 27:40.387
We going to get
that loan no problem.

27:40.420 --> 27:43.685
Okay. But the loan officer
will be here soon,

27:43.730 --> 27:46.119
so how much did he say we could
get for this harvest?

27:46.160 --> 27:48.048
You ain't going
to believe this.

27:48.100 --> 27:53.220
He said we looking to make
$1.5 million from our 300 acres.

27:53.270 --> 27:55.033
You're kidding?

27:55.070 --> 27:56.958
No. We about to be rich!

27:57.000 --> 28:00.163
If the cane stays dry and we
have a good grind with the mill,

28:00.210 --> 28:01.438
that's what
we're gomg to make.

28:01.480 --> 28:04.847
What did he say if all
800 acres were harvested?

28:04.880 --> 28:06.347
- In a good year?
- Yeah.

28:06.380 --> 28:07.779
( laughs )

28:07.820 --> 28:09.139
Check this.

28:12.120 --> 28:15.385
We could bring in
$4.2 million.

28:16.820 --> 28:18.185
Look, I knew
we would do good,

28:18.230 --> 28:20.289
but I didn't know
it was that kind of money.

28:20.330 --> 28:21.888
Okay, calm down.

28:21.930 --> 28:24.319
Oh, now, come on, Charley.
Can't we celebrate?

28:24.370 --> 28:26.099
We'll celebrate once
the loan comes in

28:26.130 --> 28:27.836
and we figure out
where to grind our cane.

28:27.870 --> 28:29.337
(vehicle approaching )

28:30.500 --> 28:31.967
I'll check that out.

28:40.920 --> 28:42.717
We got to handle this.

28:51.790 --> 28:53.018
Mr. Boudreaux,

28:53.060 --> 28:54.322
what are you
doing here?

28:54.360 --> 28:55.827
Mrs. West.

28:55.860 --> 28:57.225
And you must be Ralph Angel.

28:57.260 --> 28:59.023
- I'm--
- I know who you are.

28:59.070 --> 29:01.095
What business
you got here?

29:01.140 --> 29:02.937
Well, never heard back
from you with an answer

29:02.970 --> 29:04.369
regarding our offer.
Thought I'd pay you a visit.

29:04.410 --> 29:06.207
My siblings and I
talked it over,

29:06.240 --> 29:07.832
and a few things
came to light--

29:07.880 --> 29:09.939
Ralph Angel:
We ain't selling our farm.

29:09.980 --> 29:13.245
So, y'all Landrys
and Boudreauxs,

29:13.280 --> 29:16.738
y'all can quit trying
to buy it out from under us.

29:19.150 --> 29:22.381
Are you certain
of this decision?

29:24.030 --> 29:25.486
Yes, we are.

29:32.430 --> 29:35.194
How you think you're going
to make harvest?

29:37.600 --> 29:39.067
Excuse me?

29:39.110 --> 29:40.975
You need a mill
to grind your cane.

29:41.010 --> 29:43.001
We_own_ all the mills
in this parish.

29:43.040 --> 29:44.871
- Is that a threat?
- No.

29:44.910 --> 29:48.243
A threat would be
hypothetical.

29:50.050 --> 29:51.142
That's just fact.

29:51.190 --> 29:53.784
We got a problem,
partner? Huh?

29:55.060 --> 29:58.029
No need to get riled up.

29:59.260 --> 30:02.297
My family are reasonable
people, Mrs. West.

30:02.330 --> 30:07.996
See, your farm is smack-dab
in the middle of our land.

30:08.040 --> 30:09.359
Has been for years.

30:09.400 --> 30:11.300
I think our offer
was more than generous.

30:11.340 --> 30:14.309
Four million dollars
is a lot of money.

30:14.340 --> 30:16.228
And if you're not willing
to cooperate...

30:18.510 --> 30:19.841
things might get difficult.

30:26.020 --> 30:28.113
As difficult as you made them
for our father?

30:28.160 --> 30:31.323
It's the good ole boys club,
right?

30:31.360 --> 30:35.091
The Landrys have the money
and the power and the influence

30:35.130 --> 30:36.392
in this parish.

30:36.430 --> 30:38.068
Always have.

30:39.630 --> 30:43.339
That time is coming
to an end.

30:43.370 --> 30:48.603
I suggest you get in your car
and get off our land

30:48.640 --> 30:52.246
if you know what's best.

30:53.410 --> 30:55.469
Okay.

31:01.060 --> 31:03.210
Oh, before I forget,

31:03.260 --> 31:05.148
we got a hold
of that application

31:05.190 --> 31:08.193
the crop advisor submitted.

31:08.230 --> 31:10.892
I'm afraid your bank loan
was denied.

31:16.640 --> 31:17.902
( spits )

31:21.540 --> 31:23.405
( muttering )

31:53.170 --> 31:54.569
( indistinct chatter )

32:21.100 --> 32:23.534
Excuse me.

32:23.570 --> 32:24.707
Charley Bordelon-West.

32:24.740 --> 32:25.707
Frank Rovner.

32:25.740 --> 32:27.731
I have not had the pleasure.

32:27.770 --> 32:31.445
We have run in the same
Circles for years.

32:31.480 --> 32:33.448
I had no idea you were
from the South.

32:33.480 --> 32:37.109
Didn't have much use for a
southern accent in Los Angeles.

32:37.150 --> 32:38.583
( both laugh )

32:38.620 --> 32:40.212
Mm-mm.

32:40.250 --> 32:42.684
So, your son's going
to be a Gardini man?

32:42.720 --> 32:44.153
Starting in the fall.

32:44.190 --> 32:46.226
Now, what do you have,
a son or daughter?

32:46.260 --> 32:48.057
Daughter. Fiona.

32:48.100 --> 32:49.419
Fifteen going on 25.

32:49.460 --> 32:51.621
Oh, tell me about it.

32:51.670 --> 32:52.489
Congrats, by the way.

32:52.530 --> 32:54.339
The Stingers win
over the Grizzlies.

32:54.370 --> 32:56.065
That was impressive.

32:56.100 --> 32:58.568
It was a close one.

32:58.610 --> 32:59.736
Charley:
Thank you, Frank.

33:01.610 --> 33:04.670
I saw your husband
was back on the market.

33:04.710 --> 33:07.577
Cuban and I have a bet whether
it's the Knicks or the Nets.

33:07.610 --> 33:08.577
( laughs )

33:08.620 --> 33:11.248
It's not too late for it
to be the Stingers.

33:11.290 --> 33:12.609
Ooh, too rich for my blood.

33:12.650 --> 33:14.982
How do you know
if you don't make an offer?

33:16.560 --> 33:18.653
You're telling me a franchise
player like Davis West

33:18.690 --> 33:21.625
would come down here for
anything less than $15 million?

33:21.660 --> 33:23.753
I think there's room _
to negotiate when two parties

33:23.800 --> 33:25.392
have something to gain.

33:27.530 --> 33:31.432
After that, uh...scandal,

33:31.470 --> 33:34.303
I thought you would have
moved on as his manager.

33:34.340 --> 33:36.399
The two of you
would have parted ways.

33:40.410 --> 33:42.617
Frank, I'll be candid.

33:42.650 --> 33:46.142
I'm the CEO of a business
known as Davis West.

33:46.190 --> 33:47.418
Now, whether my product
is called

33:47.450 --> 33:50.715
"The Gentleman" or "The Gigolo,"
it all works.

33:50.760 --> 33:54.150
Just depends on how
it's packaged.

34:10.640 --> 34:12.779
* Every time
we go out dancing... *

34:12.810 --> 34:14.846
Hey, baby.

34:14.880 --> 34:16.518
( both laugh )

34:16.550 --> 34:18.211
Did you bring me
another set of hands?

34:18.250 --> 34:20.480
Aunt Vi, this is Too Sweet.
Too Sweet, this is my Aunt Vi.

34:20.520 --> 34:22.215
We hug around here, baby.

34:22.260 --> 34:23.409
( laughs )

34:23.460 --> 34:24.654
Nice to meet you,
Too Sweet.

34:24.690 --> 34:26.123
Thanks for having me, ma'am.

34:26.160 --> 34:27.752
"Miss Vi" will do just fine.

34:27.790 --> 34:29.792
Nova:
And that's my brother
Ralph Angel.

34:29.830 --> 34:31.422
Hey.

34:31.470 --> 34:33.665
And Micah and Blue.
My nephews.

34:34.600 --> 34:36.192
Ralph:
What you say?

34:37.740 --> 34:39.230
Hey, little man.

34:39.270 --> 34:40.760
Hi.

34:40.810 --> 34:42.835
- Micah.
- Too Sweet.

34:42.880 --> 34:44.438
Yeah.

34:45.710 --> 34:47.803
Miss Vi, can I go
to the bathroom?

34:47.850 --> 34:50.114
Oh, it's right there
to the left, baby.

34:53.220 --> 34:58.180
Blue, come. I'm going to show
you the new soda machine.

34:59.690 --> 35:01.499
Get your mama.

35:06.230 --> 35:08.232
Come on, Mom.
Let's go.

35:13.710 --> 35:17.498
Please don't get him
hopped up on that sugar now.

35:17.540 --> 35:19.269
Violet:
Mind your business!

35:19.310 --> 35:21.471
- ( laughing )
- You got my message?

35:21.520 --> 35:24.216
Yeah. I can't believe
Jacob Boudreaux had the nerve
to come out there like that.

35:24.250 --> 35:26.639
He's luclq I wasn't there.
I'll put a rut on that
whole family.

35:26.690 --> 35:28.783
Look, if Blue wasn't around,
it was about to go down--

35:28.820 --> 35:30.617
Have you talked to Charley?
How are we going to grind
without a mill?

35:30.660 --> 35:33.481
I don't know
and she don't know.

35:33.530 --> 35:35.691
But we got
to do something.

35:35.730 --> 35:38.528
We ain't going out
like this.

35:38.570 --> 35:40.663
I'm going to finish
hanging these lights.

35:45.240 --> 35:47.333
Can I talk to you?

35:47.370 --> 35:48.507
Is this about my mom?

35:48.540 --> 35:50.599
"Is this about my mom?"

35:50.640 --> 35:54.815
Listen, I'm not going to try
to lecture you, Micah, okay?

35:54.850 --> 35:57.216
But everything's
not black and white.

35:57.250 --> 35:58.945
Life is gray as hell.

35:58.990 --> 36:00.617
And with everything
you've been through,

36:00.650 --> 36:03.551
you know I'm telling
the truth.

36:03.590 --> 36:05.285
As you get older, you start
to see your mama and daddy

36:05.330 --> 36:07.651
as real people.

36:07.690 --> 36:09.328
And people
mess up sometimes.

36:09.360 --> 36:11.669
Well, them more
than most, but--

36:11.700 --> 36:14.237
Not true. No more than me.
No more than you.

36:16.470 --> 36:18.631
Look, your mama's been put
through the ringer.

36:18.670 --> 36:20.934
Put yourself
in her place.

36:20.970 --> 36:24.349
The betrayal.
The humiliation.

36:24.380 --> 36:26.268
Taking every arrow,

36:26.310 --> 36:28.778
while trying to stop
every arrow from hitting you.

36:30.580 --> 36:33.686
Everybody don't have
a mama like that.

36:42.500 --> 36:44.263
- What's up, man?
- What's up? What's up?

36:44.300 --> 36:45.961
I'm cool, man.

36:46.000 --> 36:47.365
You ball?

36:47.400 --> 36:49.436
Oh, no.
Not really my thing.

36:49.470 --> 36:50.960
- Aw.
- You?

36:51.000 --> 36:52.934
Oh, yeah. Yeah, I ball.

36:52.970 --> 36:54.506
All the time.

36:54.540 --> 36:56.235
So, I just want
to thank y'all

36:56.280 --> 36:59.704
for all the hard work
over the last couple of days.

36:59.750 --> 37:04.585
Clive, thank you for doing right
and making me manager.

